node.text: I’ve been asked many times what I think about @blackriflecoffee after the hit piece that the New York Times wrote about them. What do I think about one of the absolute best companies in the world? Who’s owners I know personally and therefore I know they have huge hearts from my personal experiences? Who have also put their lives on the line defending our country while serving in the military? Who support veterans causes like no other company I’ve ever seen? The company that also just so happens to make the best coffee on the planet? Here’s what I think. It’s always wise to let the main stream media do your thinking for you. You’d have to be an idiot to think The NY Times would be  dishonest. So of course I would like to publicly denounce Black Rifle Coffee for being so caring, giving so much to veterans causes, making the best coffee available, and for representing freedom. They also do absolutely nothing to support communism. Shame on them…
